            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Dayton</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 66.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-10-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 10, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Some unaccounted for obstruction of the mails has
                    caused a delay in the receipt of your despatch of the 7th of September (No. 44)
                    until this time.</p>
                <p>As I expected, you very properly anticipated my instructions on the subject of
                    the conditional execution of the treaty proposed by Mr. Thouvenel, and your
                    proceedings in that respect are entirely approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
